Cashback Programs#

Three approaches to automatic savings on card transactions. All modes work with
both default and smart spending controls.


Mode 1: Interchange Share#

Route a portion of interchange revenue to a user's savings pocket using the
existing spending_fees system:

const savingsPocket = await user.accounts.virtual.create(
  { name: 'Savings' },
  { waitLedger: true },
);

const card = await user.accounts.card.create({
  holderUrn: userUrn,
  name: 'Cashback Card',
  ledgerId: mainPocket.ledgerId,
  metadata: {
    spending_fees: [
      {
        fee_name: 'interchange_share',
        account_urn: savingsPocket.urn,
        type: 'percentage',
        value: 0.002,           // 0.2% of every purchase → savings
        category: 'custom',
      },
    ],
  },
});



Mode 2: Extra Savings#

Charge an extra percentage or flat amount per transaction and route it to a
savings pocket:

const card = await user.accounts.card.create({
  holderUrn: userUrn,
  name: 'Auto-Save Card',
  ledgerId: mainPocket.ledgerId,
  metadata: {
    cashback_programs: [
      {
        program_name: 'savings_5pct',
        type: 'extra_savings',
        target_pocket_urn: savingsPocket.urn,
        fee_type: 'percentage',
        value: 0.05,            // 5% surcharge → savings
      },
    ],
  },
});


For flat amounts, set fee_type: 'flat' and value to the fixed amount in local
currency (e.g., 1.0 for $1 per transaction).


Mode 3: Round Up#

Round every purchase up to the next whole unit. A $34.70 purchase becomes $35.00
— the extra $0.30 goes to the target pocket:

const card = await user.accounts.card.create({
  holderUrn: userUrn,
  name: 'Round-Up Card',
  ledgerId: mainPocket.ledgerId,
  metadata: {
    cashback_programs: [
      {
        program_name: 'spare_change',
        type: 'round_up',
        target_pocket_urn: savingsPocket.urn,
      },
    ],
  },
});



Combined Programs#

Stack multiple programs on the same card:

metadata: {
  cashback_programs: [
    {
      program_name: 'auto_save',
      type: 'extra_savings',
      target_pocket_urn: savingsPocket.urn,
      fee_type: 'percentage',
      value: 0.03,              // 3% surcharge → savings
    },
    {
      program_name: 'spare_change',
      type: 'round_up',
      target_pocket_urn: roundUpPocket.urn,
    },
  ],
}



CashbackProgram#

interface CashbackProgram {
  program_name: string;
  type: 'extra_savings' | 'round_up';
  target_pocket_urn: string;
  fee_type?: 'percentage' | 'flat';   // Required for extra_savings
  value?: number;                      // Rate (0.05 = 5%) or fixed amount
}


FIELD               TYPE                           REQUIRED             DESCRIPTION
program_name        string                         Yes                  Unique name for the program
type                'extra_savings' | 'round_up'   Yes                  Savings mode
target_pocket_urn   string                         Yes                  Pocket URN receiving the surcharge
fee_type            'percentage' | 'flat'          extra_savings only   How to compute the surcharge
value               number                         extra_savings only   Rate (0.05 = 5%) for percentage, or fixed local-currency
                                                                        amount for flat


How Cashback Works#

 1. The CashbackDecorator calculates surcharges from each configured program
 2. The transaction amount is inflated (original + surcharges) for the balance
    check
 3. fee_basis is set to the original amount — interchange and FX fees are
    computed on the original, not the inflated total
 4. The base spending control (default or smart) debits the full inflated amount
 5. Surcharge movements route funds from the treasury to the target pockets
 6. A cashback_surcharge webhook event reports the breakdown


Cashback Webhook Event#

When cashback programs are active, a cashback_surcharge event is delivered
alongside the standard purchase event:

{
  "account_urn": "did:bloque:account:card:usr-abc:crd-123",
  "transaction_id": "ctx-200kXoaEJLNzcsvNxY1pmBO7fEx",
  "type": "authorization",
  "direction": "debit",
  "event": "cashback_surcharge",
  "surcharge_total": 1.341,
  "programs": [
    { "name": "auto_save", "type": "extra_savings", "amount": 1.041 },
    { "name": "spare_change", "type": "round_up", "amount": 0.30 }
  ]
}


Amounts are in the merchant's local currency. Surcharges do not appear in
fee_breakdown.


Cashback Refunds#

On credit adjustments (refunds), cashback surcharges are reversed
proportionally. A 50% refund returns 50% of each program's surcharge from the
savings pockets. No separate webhook event is sent for cashback reversals.


Best Practices#

 1.  User Sessions: Always connect to a user session
 2.  KYC First: Ensure users complete KYC verification
 3.  Meaningful Names: Help users identify their cards
 4.  Check Status: Verify card status before use
 5.  Security: Never store full card numbers
 6.  Error Handling: Use try-catch blocks
 7.  Test in Sandbox: Test thoroughly before production
 8.  Idempotent Webhooks: Always handle duplicate deliveries gracefully
 9.  Fee Awareness: Include fee breakdowns in transaction receipts shown to
     users
 10. Smart Spending Budgets: Use pocket-based spending controls to help users
     manage category budgets


